<br>
I'm just curious as to what type of gear I should be shooting for in order to maintain efficiency in both pvp and pve situations.<br>
<br>
Here is what I have.<br>
I am a dark elf btw =)<br>
<br>
Neck: Orc Fang Necklace<br>
Face: Split Paw Hide Mask<br>
Head: nada =(<br>
Ears: nada <br>
Arms: Small Ringmail<br>
Wrists:  Bracer of Erollisi (which I switch with a +7 mr bracer when the situation warrents) and another +7 mr bracer.<br>
Back: nada<br>
Feet: nada<br>
Legs: Small banded<br>
Chest: Dwarven Ringmail Tunic<br>
Shoulder: banded<br>
<br>
I am dualwielding a bloodclaw and a tentacle whip ;p<br>
<br>
I've a chill dagger which I switch in for resists, and a wraithbone hammer which I use for the strength bonus and to keep blunt up.<br>
<br>
I'm also looking to fill the shoulder slot up with a bloodstained mantle if and when I can find someone selling one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Right now, I've about 1000pp (buy and sell baby!) =) probably 700pp or so more after I sell the Plat Ruby Veil*assuming it sells for what people tell me it will*...sitting around burning a whole in my pocket =) Suggestions as to where I could spend it?<br>
<br>
A serrated bone dirk perhaps?  I'm not entirely sure if I can afford a Slime Coated Harpoon.  Or a better slashing weapon? =)<br>
<br>
I've left the other slots empty, as I've simply no clue as to what to put there =)*doesn't want to waste money on banded, only to buy something else right after*<br>
<br>
Also, I've read a couple threads regarding throwing vs archery.<br>
<br>
Initially I took up throwing, it semt more 'roguely'.  But the throwing dagger range, well it's none too great =)And the first bow I could make gave me a range of 50.  With the arrows I'm using now, I've a range of 150 =).<br>
And if I were to use the more expensive throwing weapons.  I've seen people talk about the forged spears?  About 5 gold a throw?  I'm a little too cheap for that =)<br>
<br>
Money aside however, I know that throwing has a chance to crit, deadly and assasinate, this combined with a lower delay would make better for interrupts?  Do ranged weapons interrupt spells? =)  Does assasinate work on pcs?  <br>
<br>
Suggestions? =)<br>
<br>
Thanks!<br>
<br>
