<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.13thshadowcompany.com/svimages/new_post.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/22/01 4:28:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oopsie =)</span><hr size=1> Neck: Platinum Wolf's Eye NecklaceFace: Split Paw Hide Mask<br>
Head: RS Coif <br>
Arms: RS Arms<br>
Wrists: 2 Gold Wolf's Eye Bracelets<br>
Back: Polar Bear Cloaks OR Lizardscale Cload<br>
Feet: RS Boots<br>
Legs: RS Legs<br>
Chest: Dwarven Ringmail Tunic OR Sarnak Emblazaned Tabbard<br>
Shoulder: Bloodstained Mantle<br>
Hands: Split Paw Gloves<br>
Fingers: HP Ring (if on PVP servers, as pulling off an HP ring saves from EXP loss as well as prohibits corpse looting)<br>
Ears: 2 Earrings of Fire Reflection<br>
Range: Runed Bone Fork<br>
Waste: Split Paw Belt<br>
Face: Mask of Deception<br>
<br>
I just suggested RS in places I couldn't think of anything better, because most RS has resists on it and the AC is not bad either. Put your MOD on your face for the 7MR.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><center><img src="http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/chrome30.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufricka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fricka</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Elegant_Rogue/shanks/teenyknot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/01 1:16:20 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Elegant_Rogue/Sigs/4FrickaNEWlt.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oopsie =)</span><hr size=1> Get used to switching out gear throughout your rogue career.<br>
<br>
It's best to have a PvE suit and a PvP suit because sometimes just having a few pieces to switch makes a huge difference.<br>
<br>
I generally travel with my full MR gear on and go to my PvE stuff only after making sure the area is secure. <p><table border=0 align=left width=100%>
