</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/01 1:42:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oopsie =)</span><hr size=1> i generally remove the majority of my non-visible equipment, and swap in mr bracers and other mr gear when i'm pvp'ing or traveling in outdoor zones in faydwer, antonica, and velious.  I keep ravenscale on for the resists and the look, it's easy enough to bag 5 or 6 items before you die.  If i were on tallon zek, i would keep everything on and merely swap out normal gear for mr gear.<br>
(by the way.. fricka.. what's with the militia tunic fetish? nostalgia?) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulirintz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lirin TZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/01 3:35:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oopsie =)</span><hr size=1> i was going to say exactly what Frika said on the gear issue.<br>
<br>
and yes, throwing weapons inturupt spells(i learned this the hard way aginst a yellow monk when i was playing my druid).  i keep a couple stacks of sheriuken(sp?) on me because as far as i know they have the lowest delay of any throwing weapons. <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/drunkmonkus/CoNForever.jpg"> 
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceescritdabossalini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceescrit da Bossalini</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/01 12:09:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oopsie =)</span><hr size=1> For the money you have to spend, here's what I'll suggest (PvP Gear only, keep your PvE (or STR/AC) gear in a bag to swap in when exping:<br>
<br>
Neck: Platinum Wolf's Eye or Ry`gorr Neck<br>
Head: BI Crown<br>
Arms: RS/Kylong Arms<br>
Wrists: 2 Gold Wolf's Eye Bracelets<br>
Back: Cloak of the Icebear (by far THE best cloak you can get for the price)<br>
Feet: RS/Ry`gorr/Sentry Boots<br>
Legs: RS/Ry`gorr Legs<br>
Chest: Dwarven Ringmail Tunic (the extra resists on this by FAR outwiegh that of the SET if you can wear it)<br>
Shoulder: Bloodstained Mantle (Definately get one of these and always wear it.  If anything, make a lighty mule and put some plat on him to buy this kind of stuff in Gfay for cheap)<br>
Hands: Cured Tizmak/Ravenscale Gloves (RS is the best)<br>
Fingers: AC 4 +10 sv Fire or Cold Rings<br>
Ears: 2 Earrings of Fire/Magic Reflection<br>
Range: Bah, use a bow.  (get a nice fast bow with decent damage and get that archery skill up.  throwing doesn't hold a candle in most situations)<br>
Waste: Split Paw/Sentry Belt<br>
Face: Mask of Deception (you're a dark elf, this should be damn easy for you to get on your server)<br>
<br>
Stats, in order of Importance:<br>
<br>
MAGIC RESIST<br>
MAGIC RESIST<br>
MAGIC RESIST<br>
Fire Resist<br>
Cold Resist<br>
Amor Class<br>
<br>
All the rest is chicken fodder until higher levels, regardless of what anyone tells you.  Depending on what level you are, shoot for Magic Resist from 75-100s and Cold/Fire 75 and you should be almost unstoppable to casters pre-level 40s<br>
<br>
If you're goin toe to toe with a warrior, rogue, or monk, throw on all the armor class ya got if you know there is no one around to root/snare you.  If you see an SK or Ranger with a big 2 handed weapon that's even or higher level than you, run! <p><font size=4 face=Times New Roman, serif><b>Ceescrit Bossalini</font><BR>
